  "label": "The Interval Bunkroom",
  "description": "The Interval Bunkroom forms a compact lodging cell carved behind the Null Cantina’s sound-baffling panels, its glass-dark composite walls scored with the Anchorage’s repeating grids. A recessed sleeping niche is set into the latticework, bounded by matte partitions that absorb glare and enforce the room’s measured geometry. Rectilinear filaments run in a tight ceiling course, casting hard-edged light that subdivides the floor into strict intervals. A narrow slit-aperture of mooring-view glass admits the disciplined mural of void-channels without breaking the room’s controlled quiet.",
